Good Morning Georgetown Families,
Over the weekend, the Ohio Department of Health issued a new order about face masks that will directly affect staff and students. Below you will find a link to the order, but in essence it states that every person will wear a face mask, unless they meet the exemption listed. If you have any questions, please contact your building principal.
https://tinyurl.com/yykvahyw

https://tinyurl.com/y54l7skr

Thank you for patience and support.
Brad Winterod
Superintendent of the Georgetown exempted Village School District

post_text: In light of the governor’s announcement today, we will be closing schools on 3/13/2020 to allow the teaching staff to complete lesson plans for the mandatory 3 week school closure. All students/staff will return to school on 3/16 to make final arrangements for the mandatory closing. All schools in the state of Ohio will be closed 3/17/2020 to 4/3/2020. Schools are slated to reopen on 4/6/2020. During this closure all athletic events and practices will be cancelled. All school buildings will be closed for any type of use from outside groups.
